pha}$. We also propose families of\n(super)conformal higher-derivative non-gauge actions and new superconformal\noperators in any curved space. Finally, through considerations based on\nsupersymmetry, we argue that the conformal spin-3 field should always be\naccompanied by a conformal spin-2 field in order to ensure gauge invariance in\na Bach-flat background.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 May 2020 12:45:23 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 29 May 2020 06:07:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 19 Aug 2020 08:31:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-02"}
